participating-org.narrative:
ADCR - Association for the Development of Rural Communities, based in Gaza Province, emerged in 1990 to promote the exchange of experiences and lessons learned with other similar organizations, both national and international level.
The year 1990 was considered pilot year and the main objective was to test the organizational capacity to implement programs, capacity management, identification of target groups, as well as the treatment of administrative affairs, including its legalization.
ADCR is composed of 37 members of which 28 are singles and the other associations.
 ADCR was founded in 1991.
Areas of intervention:
# Agriculture and livestock;
# Beekeeping;
# Micro credit and finances;
# Shelter;
# Water and sanitation;
# Advocacy;
# Emergencies response, for example, drought in 2012/2013 - Chigubo District;
# Education and literacy.

Overall Objective: To improve the institutional capacity, organizational,and material to better DRR intervention in Gaza Province.

Results:
# Improvedcapacity of ADCR for strategic management of humanitarian action and RRD;
# Developed skills to respond emergencies and implementing DRR projects;
# ADCR strengthened in humanitarian logistic capacities.
